We ("us", "we", or "our") operates FoodAI application(the "Service").
    This page informs you of our policies regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of personal data when you use our Service and the choices you have associated with that data.
    We use your data to provide and improve the Service. By using the Service, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy. Unless otherwise defined in this Privacy Policy, terms used in this Privacy Policy have the same meanings as in our Terms of Service.
Information Collection And Use
Data collected from the app is not linked to your identity. We don't use the data for tracking purposes. We collect several different types of information for various purposes to provide and improve our Service to you.
Types of Data Collected
Purchases
Product Interactions
Crash Data
Performance Data
User diet data including: Age, Dietary goal, Dietary restrictions, Alergies, Health conditions, Target weight, Gender, Weight, Height, Name, Email address, User IDs, User's event
To use the camera-based food logging feature in the FoodAI app, we require access to your device's camera. This allows you to photograph your meals for nutritional analysis. Images are used for identifying and logging food items. Camera access can be managed and revoked at any time through your device settings. By using this feature, you consent to our processing of these images as described.
Use of Data
The app uses the collected data for various purposes:
To provide analysis or valuable information so that we can improve the Service
To monitor the usage of the Service
To detect, prevent and address technical issues
To provide and maintain the Service
To provide customer care and support
Transfer Of Data
Your information may be transferred to — and maintained on — computers located outside of your state, province, country or other governmental jurisdiction where the data protection laws may differ than those from your jurisdiction.
    If you are located outside United States and choose to provide information to us, please note that we transfer the data to United States and process it there.
    Your consent to this Privacy Policy followed by your submission of such information represents your agreement to that transfer.
    The app will take all steps reasonably necessary to ensure that your data is treated securely and in accordance with this Privacy Policy and no transfer of your data will take place to an organization or a country unless there are adequate controls in place including the security of your data.
Disclosure Of Data
Legal Requirements
The app may disclose your data in the good faith belief that such action is necessary to:
To comply with a legal obligation
To protect and defend the rights or property of the app
To prevent or investigate possible wrongdoing in connection with the Service
To protect the personal safety of users of the Service or the public
To protect against legal liability
Security Of Data
The security of your data is important to us, but remember that no method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your data, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
Apple Health Integration
FoodAI integrates with Apple Health to enable secure, context-driven data exchange between your Health app and our Service. With your explicit consent, FoodAI can read and write the following health metrics:
Iron:
Tracks your iron intake, vital for oxygen transport and energy metabolism.
Magnesium:
Monitors magnesium consumption, important for muscle function and metabolic regulation.
Potassium:
Records potassium levels from your diet, supporting heart health and fluid balance.
Protein:
Tracks protein consumption, essential for muscle repair, growth, and recovery.
Saturated Fat:
Measures saturated fat intake to help manage cholesterol levels and support heart health.
Sodium:
Monitors sodium consumption, key for maintaining fluid balance and healthy blood pressure.
Total Fat:
Aggregates total fat intake, providing insights into energy balance and dietary quality.
Vitamin A:
Tracks vitamin A levels, essential for vision, immune support, and skin health.
Vitamin B12:
Monitors vitamin B12 consumption, crucial for nerve function and red blood cell production.
Vitamin C:
Records vitamin C intake, important for immune defense and antioxidant protection.
Vitamin D:
Tracks vitamin D levels, vital for bone health and immune system support.
Water:
Monitors water consumption, essential for hydration and overall bodily function.
Zinc:
Records zinc intake, important for immune function and various metabolic processes.
Caffeine:
Monitors caffeine consumption, helping to manage energy levels and alertness.
Calcium:
Tracks calcium intake, essential for building strong bones and supporting muscle function.
Carbohydrates:
Measures carbohydrate consumption, providing the energy needed for daily activities.
Dietary Cholesterol:
Monitors cholesterol intake to support heart health and balanced nutrition.
Dietary Energy:
Aggregates the total energy from your food, helping maintain daily activity levels.
Dietary Sugar:
Tracks sugar consumption to manage energy spikes and maintain metabolic balance.
Fiber:
Records fiber intake, crucial for digestive health and sustained energy release.
Folate:
Monitors folate levels, important for cell repair and overall metabolic function.
Exercise Data:
Records of your physical activities that help track workouts and progress.
Total Calories Burned:
The cumulative energy expenditure during activities, used to monitor your fitness outcomes.
Height:
Your recorded height, essential for tailoring health insights and personal recommendations.
Weight:
Your weight information, which is crucial for tracking changes.
Body Fat Percentage:
Data reflecting your body composition, used to assess overall health and fitness progress.
We request access to these metrics only when needed—such as during a weight entry or profile update—to ensure our requests are clearly related to the current context. Standard Apple permission dialogs provide clear explanations for these data requests, and you can manage your permissions at any time in Settings > Privacy > Health.
All health data is handled with the utmost care and protected using industry-standard security measures. We only access your data with your permission, ensuring your privacy and trust remain our highest priority.
Service Providers
We may employ third party companies and individuals to facilitate our Service ("Service Providers"), to provide the Service on our behalf, to perform Service-related services or to assist us in analyzing how our Service is used.
      These third parties have access to your data only to perform these tasks on our behalf and are obligated not to disclose or use it for any other purpose.
Links To Other Sites
Our Service may contain links to other sites that are not operated by us. If you click on a third party link, you will be directed to that third party's site. We strongly advise you to review the Privacy Policy of every site you visit.
      We have no control over and assume no responsibility for the content, privacy policies or practices of any third party sites or services.
Children's Privacy
Our Service does not address anyone under the age of 18 ("Children").
      We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from anyone under the age of 18. If you are a parent or guardian and you are aware that your Children has provided us with data, please contact us. If we become aware that we have collected data from children without verification of parental consent, we take steps to remove that information from our servers.
Data Sharing for Refund Management
We may collect and share consumption data related to your use of the app with Apple’s App Store Server to process refund requests. This includes:
Time spent using the app,
Content accessed or completed,
Lifetime purchase history and usage frequency,
Previous refund history (if applicable).
This data is shared securely and only when required to assist in refund decisions initiated through Apple’s App Store.
Changes To This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.
      We will update the "effective date" at the top of this Privacy Policy.
      You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Changes to this Privacy Policy are effective when they are posted on this page.
